like the form and the way the dance describes nature. It is beautiful and lyrical. It touches my heart and I decided to leave everything behind and follow my passion,\" he narrated. \"Being very traditional people, a boy taking to dancing was a strict no in my family, but when my parents watched the performance of my guru Rahul Acharya they agreed. Being the first male Odissi dancer in West Indies, I have a lot of opportunities in my country, where the dance form is getting popular,\" he said.Similarly, mother-daughter duo Eleonora and Angelina have become ambassadors of Odissi dance in Russia with their performances for the last one decade. \"Through our performance we want people of Russia to learn the spiritual intimacy of Indian and Russian people, to give a true vision of Odissi dance embodying principles of goodness, humanism and contribute to greater understanding of each other,\" said 47-year-old Eleonora.", "source": "toi", "date": "2012-12-25"}
